SIMPLE: discommend
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Discommend
<hw>Dis`com*mend"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To mention with disapprobation; to blame; to disapprove.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By commending something in him that is good, and
<qex>discommending</qex> the same fault in others.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 421 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To expose to censure or ill favor; to put out of the
good graces of any one.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A compliance will <qex>discommend</qex> me to Mr. Coventry.</q>
<rj><qau>Pepys.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discommendable</ent>⟦br⟧
